3:
There he broke the arrows of the bow,
\q the shield, the sword, and the other weapons of war.
\qs Selah\qs*
4:
You shine brightly and reveal your glory,
\q as you descend from the mountains, where you killed your victims.
\q
6:
At your rebuke, God of Jacob,
\q both rider and horse fell asleep.
\q
7:
You, yes you, are to be feared;
\q who can stand in your sight when you are angry?
9:
when you, God, arose to execute judgment
\q and to save all the oppressed of the earth.
\qs Selah\qs*
10:
Surely your angry judgment against humanity will bring you praise;
\q you gird yourself with what is left of your anger.
11:
Make vows to Yahweh your God and keep them.
\q May all who surround him bring gifts to him who is to be feared.
\q
12:
He cuts off the spirit of the princes;
\q he is feared by the kings of the earth.
76:
\m
\d For the chief musician, on stringed instruments. A psalm of Asaph, a song.
\q
